00:00:14.199 --> 00:00:18.199
And what can we benefit or how can we benefit from it today?

00:00:19.199 --> 00:00:24.199
But let's first look at a prayer that relates to this account offered by Jesus.

00:00:24.199 --> 00:00:27.199
Please turn with me to John chapter 17.

00:00:29.989 --> 00:00:34.990
And we'll recall in this account, Jesus was about to be arrested, tried and executed.

00:00:35.990 --> 00:00:38.990
But he was deeply concerned about his followers.

00:00:38.990 --> 00:00:42.990
So notice the request that he made of his father.

00:00:43.990 --> 00:00:45.990
That's verse 15.

00:00:45.990 --> 00:00:54.990
I do not request that you take them out of the world, but that you watch over them because of the wicked one.

00:00:55.990 --> 00:01:00.990
Now notice that Jesus said, watch over them. Those three key words.

00:01:00.990 --> 00:01:02.990
What does that mean?

00:01:02.990 --> 00:01:08.989
What means to not be a policeman, but to have a protective care of someone?

00:01:08.989 --> 00:01:14.989
Now the original language word actually means to guard from loss or injury by keeping an eye on.

00:01:15.989 --> 00:01:20.989
So we think about a shepherd that watches over his sheep during the night.

00:01:21.989 --> 00:01:27.989
Or a caring father that looks out for his little children to prevent them from getting harmed.

00:01:27.989 --> 00:01:33.989
Well, that's the sense that Jesus had in trying to get protection for his followers.

00:01:33.989 --> 00:01:37.989
And we're sure that Jehovah heard that selfless prayer.

00:01:37.989 --> 00:01:45.989
Now with that prayer in mind, let's fast forward to a few years later and Paul's second missionary tour.

00:01:45.989 --> 00:01:49.989
The spirit has directed Paul to step over into Macedonia.

00:01:49.989 --> 00:01:52.989
Then to Athens and then to Corinth.

00:01:52.989 --> 00:01:54.989
And that's where we pick up the action.

00:01:54.989 --> 00:01:57.989
So if you turn to Acts chapter 18,

00:01:57.989 --> 00:02:04.989
we're going to see that Paul has become intensely occupied with the word in verse five.

00:02:04.989 --> 00:02:06.989
Now he faces headwinds.

00:02:06.989 --> 00:02:11.990
Headwinds are strong opposition from the Jews.

00:02:11.990 --> 00:02:13.990
What does he do?

00:02:13.990 --> 00:02:15.990
Well, he has to face the situation.

00:02:15.990 --> 00:02:18.990
Does he stay there and that assignment sticking it out?

00:02:18.990 --> 00:02:20.990
Perhaps risking his life?

00:02:20.990 --> 00:02:23.990
Or does he try to go to say for harbours?

00:02:23.990 --> 00:02:27.990
A safe for city where the situation is much calmer?

00:02:27.990 --> 00:02:29.990
Well, surely this stressed out Paul.

00:02:29.990 --> 00:02:33.990
And he would besiege Jehovah about this matter.

00:02:33.990 --> 00:02:36.990
But notice the answer that he receives in verse nine.

00:02:36.990 --> 00:02:42.270
It says more over the Lord said to Paul in a vision by night.

00:02:42.270 --> 00:02:45.270
Do not be afraid.

00:02:45.270 --> 00:02:50.270
But keep on speaking and do not keep silent.

00:02:50.270 --> 00:02:52.270
For I am with you.

00:02:52.270 --> 00:02:55.270
And no man will assault you to harm you.

00:02:55.270 --> 00:02:58.270
For I have many people in this city.

00:02:58.270 --> 00:03:01.270
And did you see what the Lord Jesus said?

00:03:01.270 --> 00:03:06.270
He said, do not be afraid.

00:03:06.270 --> 00:03:08.270
I am with you.

00:03:08.270 --> 00:03:12.270
Well, how that must have reassured the apostle Paul.

00:03:12.270 --> 00:03:14.270
He was stressed.

00:03:14.270 --> 00:03:16.270
But this must have calmed him down.

00:03:16.270 --> 00:03:19.270
Because he knew that he was going to be well cared for.

00:03:19.270 --> 00:03:21.270
He was being looked out for.

00:03:21.270 --> 00:03:25.270
